<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[2067,2665,2290,2719]" pageId="24" pageNumber="82">
Until recently, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pohle" authorityYear="1943" box="[2296,2410,2369,2402]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="82" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ophiodon">ophiodon</taxonomicName>
was included in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matschie" authorityYear="1894" box="[2070,2227,2409,2442]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="82" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Scotonycteris</taxonomicName>
, but it was moved to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1910" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Casinycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="82" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Casinycteris</taxonomicName>
based on analyses of morphology and cytochrome-b sequences. Sequences differed by 14:4% between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pohle" authorityYear="1943" box="[2417,2531,2528,2561]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="82" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ophiodon">ophiodon</taxonomicName>
and S. zenkeriand 7-7% and 8-4% between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pohle" authorityYear="1943" box="[2549,2663,2568,2601]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Scotonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="82" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ophiodon">ophiodon</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1910" box="[2136,2283,2615,2640]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Casinycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="82" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="argynnis">C. argynnis</taxonomicName>
and C. campomaanenss, respectively. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
